1.text: Rinse the zucchini to remove any dirt.

2.text: Chop off the stem and blossom ends with a sharp knife.

3.text: Chop off small cylinders of desired thickness.

4.text: Cut the zucchini in half before slicing for a quicker-cooking dish.

5.text: Wash the zucchini before you cut.

6.text: Cut off the stem and blossom ends.

7.text: Carefully cut the zucchini into 3-4 vertical strips.

8.text: Slice each strip into 3 thinner strips.

9.text: Turn the zucchini and cut crosswise to make cubes.

10.text: Rinse the zucchini and cut off the ends.

11.text: Cut the zucchini lengthwise into 1⁄4 inch (0.64 cm) thick planks.

12.text: Lay one plank flat and cut the top off at an angle.

13.text: Continue cutting at the same angle, making matchstick-sized pieces.

14.text: Rinse the zucchini and cut off both ends.

15.text: Chop the zucchini in quarters and remove the seeds.

16.text: Grate one quarter at a time against the large holes on a box grater.

17.text: Place the grated zucchini in a colander.

18.text: Mix in 1 teaspoon (4.9 mL) of salt and let it sit.

19.text: Place the grated zucchini onto a paper towel-covered plate.
